#title()[Summary of activities, 2 March 2026]

\


*Plan & deliverables:* At the outset of this week, I met with Bin to establish a plan for the week. We determined that I would focus on three primary deliverables for this week, detailed below: (1) primer designs targeting _GBA1_ N370S; (2) a graphical abstract for the Familial PD INTERACT document; (3) a battery of tests to evaluate _GBA1_ correction _in vitro_. Additional focuses included establishing long-term goals of increasing my fluency with gene editing and iPSC reprogramming techniques and literature, as well as completing my onboarding. 

\


= N370S primer designs

I designed two primers targeting the _GBA1_ N370S mutation based on project parameters that we established: an amplicon length between 200--700 bp incorporating intronic differences between _GBA1_ and the pseudogene _GBAP1_ to facilitate their bioinformatic distinction downstream. I designed these primers using NCBI primer-BLAST; the exact method and final primers are detailed in the #underline()[attached document.] With Bin's approval, I emailed these to Kiara (David Liu Lab) for her feedback and ordered these, along with Kiara's L444P primers, from GeneWiz.

= INTERACT graphical abstract

I consulted with Bin to draft a suitable graphical abstract for incorporation into the Familial PD INTERACT document. We determined that hewing to Bin's original design on the project workflow made sense, with a particular point of emphasis on the one main addition to this workflow (for which we are seeking approval): the gene editing component ("One-step strategy"). Once Bin had approved my draft, I rendered the final image by hand and assembled the figure in PowerPoint to ensure it will be easily manipulable for future presentations. My final edit ensured that the depiction of the reprogramming factors is more identifiably mRNA per my discussion with Bin. The final figure is #underline()[attached] at the end of this document.

= _In vitro_ battery for _GBA1_ correction

I designed a battery of tests to verify recovery of functional deficits following _GBA1_ correction _in vitro_ based on a survery of the literature. These tests, along with other candidate tests, are summarized in the #underline()[attached] document.

= Cell culture

I also began my training to culture fibroblasts and hiPSCs with Bin and Tatyana. I observed media changes last week and on Monday, and on Tuesday I observed Tatyana passaging two 6-cm. dishes of PD05 mR01 hiPSCs. On Wednesday, I passaged PD05 mR03 hiPSCs 1:1 into two 6-cm. dishes under Bin and Tatyana's observation. I independently conducted media changes for these two lines on Thursday and Friday (as detailed on my LabArchives, with the accompanying worksheets). I also acted as verifier for Bin while she passaged and cryopreserved fibroblasts on Tuesday and prepared samples for karyotyping (00W2D2 DAPs; PD05-eB01R11-P20 and eB01R42-P2 hiPSCs) on Friday.

= Other tasks

I completed my onboarding process, including troubleshooting my Outlook mailbox, email address domain, and card access to the lab. I corrected the hiPSC passaging worksheet (as a separate copy on Teams) and placed several orders (Staples: binders, flash drives; LabSuit: P/S, MEM-NEAA).